        "title": "Webb reveals millions of stars in nearby galaxy",
        "authors": [
            {
                "name": "ESA",
                "socials": null
            }
        ],
        "url": "https://www.esa.int/Science_Exploration/Space_Science/Webb/Webb_reveals_millions_of_stars_in_nearby_galaxy",
        "image_url": "https://www.esa.int/var/esa/storage/images/esa_multimedia/images/2026/07/centaurus_a_miri_image/27358464-1-eng-GB/Centaurus_A_MIRI_image_card_full.jpg",
        "news_site": "ESA",
        "summary": "In new images from the NASA/ESA/CSA James Webb Space Telescope to celebrate its fourth science anniversary, a familiar galaxy transforms into something far richer, and far more complex, than ever seen before. Webb\u2019s unprecedented sensitivity across near- and mid-infrared wavelengths cuts through the thick lanes of dust that obscure Centaurus A\u2019s centre in visible light, showing a densely packed tapestry of individual stars and an active, everchanging galaxy. These images mark four years of better-than-anticipated performance and successful science operations for the most powerful space telescope in history.",
